    "The process is different from the pure CNN (i.e.",
    "the aforementioned EfficientNet) that takes the average of all frames for deepfake detection as in the transfer learning process.",
    "The GRU component has thus 1,280 latent dimensions and 1,280 hidden layers as the layer configurations in this study.The optimizer used is ADAM that combines features of optimization algorithms such as RMSProp and ADAGrad.",
    "It is used to adjust the learning rate for each weight on the fly using exponential weighted moving average to get the first and second moments of the gradient estimates [56].",
    "The loss function opted is cross-entropy loss."
